This paper is about deep learning models for RGB-D semantic segmentation, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel fusion structure and a residual fusion block to model the interdependencies between the RGB and depth data, which involves learning complementary features and extracting modality-specific features. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
